problem_statement: Topic : AI-Driven AR Physiotherapy and Scar Massage Therapy for Enhanced Cancer Rehabilitation  According to the World Health Organization (WHO), 1 in 3 people worldwide will require rehabilitation at some point in their lives due to injury, illness, or chronic conditions. Additionally, studies show that 50–90% of patients undergoing major medical treatments, such as surgery or chemotherapy, experience pain, mobility issues, and scarring complications that hinder recovery. Despite this, access to effective physiotherapy and rehabilitation remains limited, leading to prolonged recovery, reduced quality of life, and increased healthcare burdens.  We propose an Augmented Reality (AR)-powered AI solution that provides interactive physiotherapy and massage techniques, with a special focus on cancer patients and post-surgical recovery. Our solution offers real-time posture guidance, personalized AR-assisted exercises, and AI-driven massage therapy. Using AI-guided AR overlays, users can learn how to massage scars in real-time to optimize skin regeneration, reduce stiffness, and improve mobility. This makes rehabilitation more engaging, effective, and accessible—helping individuals regain mobility, manage pain, and improve overall well-being from home

problem_statement: Problem Statement: AI-Powered Smart Itinerary Planner for Seamless Travel Overview: Planning a trip is often time-consuming, requiring travelers to juggle multiple apps for flights, hotels, weather updates, and local attractions. Unexpected delays, weather changes, and language barriers further complicate the experience, leading to frustration and missed opportunities.  Challenge: How can we leverage AI and real-time data to create a smart itinerary planner that adapts dynamically, enhances cultural experiences, and ensures a seamless travel experience?  Proposed Solution: Develop an AI-driven itinerary generator that personalizes travel plans based on user preferences, real-time conditions, and local insights. The platform will integrate: ✅ AI-powered recommendations based on budget, interests, and past trips. ✅ Real-time adaptability to weather changes, traffic, and local events. ✅ Hidden gems & cultural insights using NLP-based travel trend analysis. ✅ Smart ticket & booking management to streamline reservations. ✅ Offline AI assistant for translations, historical facts, and navigation. ✅ Fraud & safety detection to prevent tourist scams.  Tech Stack & Feasibility: APIs: OpenStreetMap (navigation), OpenWeather (weather), Skyscanner (flights), OpenAI/Mistral (chatbot).  AI & ML Models: NLP for recommendations, Computer Vision for auto-tagging trip photos.  Frontend & Backend: React Native / Flutter (app), Node.js/Django (backend).

problem_statement: Tourists visiting Chikkamagaluru often struggle to find personalized travel recommendations that match their group type, interests, and budget, while unreliable network coverage in remote areas makes navigation difficult. Existing platforms offer generic suggestions, lack verified ratings, and often overlook lesser-known yet valuable spots, such as remote villages, cultural sites, and natural trails.  Our AI-driven solution enhances trip planning through a short question session that captures each traveler’s preferences—such as group type, preferred trip vibe (e.g., adventure or relaxation), must-have experiences, and accommodation type (e.g., luxury resorts, budget homestays, or eco-friendly lodges). Using these inputs, we generate deeply personalized recommendations enriched with real-time data from platforms like Google Maps and Tripadvisor, alongside user reviews, local expertise, and community contributions. Unlike existing platforms, we offer AI-verified ratings (by analyzing review authenticity and sentiment) and custom itineraries tailored to individual preferences, ensuring both popular attractions and hidden gems are discovered effortlessly.  Additionally, we integrate a network coverage check to detect low-connectivity areas, automatically guiding users to download offline maps for seamless navigation, even in remote locations like trekking trails and hill stations. By combining advanced AI with local insights, our app delivers a smarter, more dependable travel experience, making Chikkamagaluru exploration effortless and tailored to every traveler.

Instead of relying on physical RFID hardware, the app allows users to tap on marked areas representing different exhibits. problem_statement: Tourists visiting a new city overwhelmingly flock to the same well‑known attractions, leading to overcrowding at major sites and leaving lesser‑known cultural gems—local artisan shops, niche museums, street art, family‑run eateries—underappreciated and economically sidelined. How might we help travelers quickly discover and experience these hidden cultural treasures, tailored to their interests, budget, and schedule?

In the healthcare industry, continuous monitoring of vital signs such as body temperature, blood pressure, and heart rate is crucial for timely diagnosis and preventive care. However, in situations where hardware sensors are unavailable or restricted, like in virtual demonstrations or constrained environments, it becomes difficult to showcase such health monitoring systems. This project presents a software-only solution that simulates sensor data to demonstrate real-time health monitoring and data analysis. The system generates realistic health readings and pushes them to a backend for analysis, alert generation, and patient tracking. This approach allows the exploration of data-driven healthcare applications — such as identifying abnormal patterns or tracking patient wellness over time — without relying on physical IoT sensors.
